From: Mohammad Farid Hendianto <hendik.suwoto@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 25 Mar 2026 13:51:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: amd: yc: Add MSI Bravo 15 C7VE to quirk table for DMIC
 support

The MSI Bravo 15 C7VE (MS-158N board) with AMD Rembrandt (Ryzen 7
7735HS) has a broken/incomplete BIOS ACPI implementation that does not
correctly expose the _WOV or AcpDmicConnected properties. As a result,
the snd_soc_acp6x_mach driver fails to probe the internal Digital
Microphone Array (DMIC) and returns -ENODEV.

Add a DMI quirk entry for the MSI Bravo 15 C7VE to the
yc_acp_quirk_table so the DMIC is properly enabled on this hardware.

Signed-off-by: Mohammad Farid Hendianto <hendik.suwoto@gmail.com>
---
 sound/soc/amd/yc/acp6x-mach.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/amd/yc/acp6x-mach.c b/sound/soc/amd/yc/acp6x-mach.c
index 1234567..abcdef0 100644
--- a/sound/soc/amd/yc/acp6x-mach.c
+++ b/sound/soc/amd/yc/acp6x-mach.c
@@ -471,6 +471,13 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id yc_acp_quirk_table[] = {
 			DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "Bravo 15 C7VF"),
 		}
 	},
+	{
+		.driver_data = &acp6x_card,
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_BOARD_VENDOR, "Micro-Star International Co., Ltd."),
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "Bravo 15 C7VE"),
+		}
+	},
 	{
 		.driver_data = &acp6x_card,
 		.matches = {
